# FounderOS (Cursor)

The open operating system for first-time founders. Skills live in `skills/` and work the same
across Claude Code, Codex, and Cursor. Full master instructions: `AGENTS.md`. Journey map:
`docs/STAGES.md`.

## Journey

```
Idea & Validation → Build / MVP → Launch & GTM → Fundraise → Operate & Scale
```

Unsure where the founder is? Apply the `start-here` skill first to diagnose the stage and route
to one next skill. Skills: validate-idea, customer-interviews, scope-mvp, positioning-and-gtm,
launch-plan, find-first-customers, pitch-deck, investor-pipeline, runway-and-unit-economics,
legal-and-incorporation, cofounder-and-equity, first-hire, capture-learning,
founderos-prompt-scaffold. Each `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` holds the method + a copy-paste prompt.

## Operating principles (enforce)

1. Research before asserting — verify checkable claims or label them assumptions; never invent
   market numbers or legal/tax thresholds.
2. A draft is not a decision — name what needs the founder's human judgement.
3. Batch, then decide — generate, gather all feedback, revise once.
4. Ask before assuming — one tight question beats the wrong artifact.
5. Route to the earliest unvalidated assumption.
6. Stay theme-agnostic — use the placeholder glossary; bake in no sector.
7. Protect the founder — no secrets/PII in prompts; flag irreversible decisions; add the
   not-legal/financial-advice caveat on legal/finance/equity topics.

## Learning loop

After a real outcome, apply `capture-learning` to append a dated lesson to `knowledge-base/`.

